rows.label: qst103904_msg0001
rows.name:
What can I do for you? Here
to pick up a delivery?

rows.label: qst103904_msg0002
rows.name:
Handling fees for sending money
from Avaritia to Iyasaki Village?

rows.label: qst103904_msg0003
rows.name:
Oh, that'd be the one from
that Rex kid. He's a good
lad, sending money home.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0004
rows.name:
We run a tight ship here, so there's
nothing shady on our end, but...

rows.label: qst103904_msg0005
rows.name:
To dock a ship at this port,
you pay a 3% port fee on
the value of the cargo.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0006
rows.name:
For large sums of cash, there's a 2%
escort fee... and the shipping cost to
the Imperial Capital is another 2%...

rows.label: qst103904_msg0007
rows.name:
So, starting from 88,200G...
about 82,166G should be
heading to the capital.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0008
rows.name: Why send it to the capital?

rows.label: qst103904_msg0009
rows.name:
Because there are no ships
from Torigo to Liberalitas.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0010
rows.name:
Not much cargo goes to
Liberalitas... It's just how it is.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0011
rows.name:
Why don't you ask the Nopon
courier in the Superbian
Empire about his fees?

rows.label: qst103904_msg0012
rows.name:
You should find him loading
cargo at Port Ananyam.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0013
rows.name:
The Nopon courier's name...
What was it again?

rows.label: qst103904_msg0014
rows.name:
Everyone just calls him
"Boss," so I've forgotten it.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0101
rows.name:
Things would be a bit cheaper
without the port fees, but...

rows.label: qst103904_msg0102
rows.name:
That money's used to maintain
the pier and hire guidance
staff, so it's necessary.
